cceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Some Hyde Park buildings are designated landmarks or located in historic districts with exterior appearance requirements. These typically regulate what appears from the street, not interior treatments. Our Hyde Park specialists are familiar with these restrictions and can recommend inside-mount treatments or those with white exterior backing that comply with most landmark guidelines.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What treatments work for Prairie-style windows in Hyde Park?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Frank Lloyd Wright-influenced Prairie-style homes in Hyde Park often have horizontal window bands and low ceilings that require treatments with clean horizontal lines. Wood blinds and roller shades work extremely well — their horizontal orientation complements Prairie-style architecture. We avoid Roman shades and drapery in these spaces as they can visually fight the horizontal emphasis.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Do you serve University of Chicago faculty housing in Hyde Park?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Yes — we've outfitted many University of Chicago faculty homes and university-owned properties in Hyde Park. We understand the co-op board requirements common in older Hyde Park buildings and can provide treatments that satisfy exterior appearance standards while delivering the interior function and aesthetics faculty homeowners want.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"What are the best treatments for casement windows in Hyde Park apartments?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Casement windows that open outward require inside-mount treatments that don't interfere with the opening mechanism. We recommend roller shades or cellular shades with inside-mount headrails positioned above the window, and bottom tracks that allow the window to open without catching the shade. We assess each window during the free in-home consultation.\"}},{\"@type\":\"Question\",\"name\":\"Can you recommend energy-efficient window treatments for older Hyde Park buildings?\",\"acceptedAnswer\":{\"@type\":\"Answer\",\"text\":\"Hyde Park has many pre-war buildings with single-pane or poorly-sealed windows. Cellular shades are our top recommendation for energy efficiency — their honeycomb construction creates an insulating air pocket that reduces heat loss in Chicago winters and heat gain in summers. Double-cell cellular shades provide approximately 40% better insulation than single-cell options.\"}}]}</script><nav aria-label=\"breadcrumb\" style=\"background:var(--surface-2);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border);padding:0.625rem 1.5rem\"><div class=\"container\"><ol style=\"display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;list-style:none;margin:0;padding:0;font-size:0.8125rem;color:var(--text-3);font-family:var(--font-body);flex-wrap:wrap\"><li><a style=\"color:var(--text-3);text-decoration:none\" href=\"/\">Home</a></li><li style=\"opacity:0.5\">/</li><li><a style=\"color:var(--text-3);text-decoration:none\" href=\"/neighborhoods\">Neighborhoods</a></li><li style=\"opacity:0.5\">/</li><li style=\"color:var(--text-2);font-weight:500\">Hyde Park</li></ol></div></nav><section style=\"position:relative;height:380px;overflow:hidden\"><img src=\"/images/neighborhoods/hydePark.jpg\" alt=\"Hyde Park Chicago neighborhood — custom window treatments by Ben&#x27;s Blinds\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block\" loading=\"eager\" fetchPriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\"/><div style=\"position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(0,0,0,0.25) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.6) 100%)\"></div><div style=\"position:absolute;inset:0;display:flex;flex-direction:column;align-items:center;justify-content:center;padding:2rem 1.5rem;text-align:center\"><p style=\"color:rgba(255,255,255,0.85);font-weight:600;font-size:0.875rem;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;margin-bottom:0.5rem;font-family:var(--fo